Lille star Renato Sanches admits he is ready to leave, but can’t confirm Milan and Arsenal are interested in signing him. Sanches sees his contract expire in June 2023 and according to Sportitalia, he has put new contract talks on hold as several big clubs in Europe have set their sights on him. The Portugal international released an interview with Metro, admitting that he is ready to leave France to begin a new chapter of his career. Olota To Hold First Annual Retreat For Awori Monarchs EKOEXCEL Marks 2022 Int’l Day Of Education However, he didn’t confirm interest from Milan or Arsenal. “Maybe Milan and Arsenal are interested, but I don’t know,” he said. “I spoke with my agent. I know which clubs are calling me, but I can’t say right now. “But I know I’m ready. If an offer comes in, I’ll find out what’s best for me.” According to Calciomercato.com, Lille want at least €30m to sell their midfield star at the end of the season. POLL The Rossoneri are already looking for a replacement for Franck Kessié. The Ivory Coast star won’t sign a contract extension with the Serie A giants, leaving San Siro as a free agent at the end of the season.